EPISODE 2: DAYDREAM

55
00:03:31,250 --> 00:03:33,330
[soldier 1] Look at that punk.

56
00:03:36,250 --> 00:03:40,300
596 DAYS UNTIL DISCHARGE

57
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:47,140
[soldier 2] Halt.

58
00:03:52,230 --> 00:03:53,310
What is your business here?

59
00:03:53,390 --> 00:03:56,310
I'm Captain Lim Ji-seop, the new aide.
Open the gate.

60
00:03:57,190 --> 00:03:58,860
Salute. Got it, sir.

61
00:03:59,820 --> 00:04:00,900
Hey.

62
00:04:01,440 --> 00:04:02,280
Yes, sir?

63
00:04:02,860 --> 00:04:03,910
"Yes, sir"?

64
00:04:06,620 --> 00:04:07,780
Aren't you a military police?

65
00:04:07,870 --> 00:04:09,200
Come here.

66
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:13,460
How can you be sure
if I'm an aide or a spy?

67
00:04:13,540 --> 00:04:14,790
Aren't you going to check?

68
00:04:15,420 --> 00:04:16,330
Sorry, sir.

69
00:04:17,630 --> 00:04:20,880
I want you to report to the squad leader
and return your leave days.

70
00:04:22,760 --> 00:04:23,630
I'm sorry, sir!

71
00:04:25,090 --> 00:04:26,470
Aren't you going to let me in?

72
00:04:27,760 --> 00:04:31,100
[soldiers] One, two, three, four…

73
00:04:32,810 --> 00:04:33,730
What is it?

74
00:04:35,440 --> 00:04:36,650
[soldier 1] Ah.

75
00:04:36,730 --> 00:04:37,770
Isn't that him?

76
00:04:37,860 --> 00:04:40,190
I heard there's a new aide coming
from the CID.

77
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:41,480
The CID?

78
00:04:41,570 --> 00:04:43,820
[pants]

79
00:04:44,780 --> 00:04:46,660
The Central Investigation Department.

80
00:04:48,910 --> 00:04:50,990
I'm asking you what that is, you punk.

81
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:55,420
[ominous music plays]

82
00:05:00,500 --> 00:05:01,500
[Beom-gu sighs]

83
00:05:02,460 --> 00:05:03,630
[commander] You're here.

84
00:05:04,220 --> 00:05:05,050
Salute.

85
00:05:05,130 --> 00:05:06,720
[commander]
Sergeant Park, what took you so long?

86
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:08,720
This is Captain Lim Ji-seop, the new aide.

87
00:05:09,220 --> 00:05:11,930
He's Sergeant First Class Park Beom-gu
who's in charge of D.P. Say hello.

88
00:05:12,020 --> 00:05:13,180
[Ji-seop] Yes.

89
00:05:13,270 --> 00:05:14,890
I look forward to working with you.

90
00:05:15,390 --> 00:05:17,020
Yes. Likewise.

91
00:05:17,100 --> 00:05:18,520
I look forward to your support.

92
00:05:19,610 --> 00:05:21,820
[commander] Sergeant Park,
you're the big shot here,

93
00:05:21,900 --> 00:05:23,530
so try your best to help him out.

94
00:05:23,610 --> 00:05:24,440
[Beom-gu] Right.

95
00:05:24,530 --> 00:05:27,700
How are things going getting our soldiers
into the special forces?

96
00:05:27,780 --> 00:05:29,410
We're doing our best to prepare, sir.

97
00:05:29,490 --> 00:05:31,120
One of the soldiers fainted
during training.

98
00:05:31,700 --> 00:05:35,040
-So we'll take it step by step.
-Good. Don't overwork them.

99
00:05:35,660 --> 00:05:38,460
But let's add mountain running
to the training.

100
00:05:39,790 --> 00:05:40,630
Okay?

101
00:05:41,840 --> 00:05:42,880
Yes, sir.

102
00:05:44,050 --> 00:05:45,170
[commander] Good.

103
00:05:45,260 --> 00:05:47,300
-[knocks on door]
-[door opens]

104
00:05:47,970 --> 00:05:49,390
-Salute.
-[commander] Yes.

105
00:05:49,470 --> 00:05:52,060
Sir, you have a tennis match
with the section leader.

106
00:05:52,140 --> 00:05:53,510
Gosh, it's time already?

107
00:05:53,600 --> 00:05:54,930
Okay.

108
00:05:55,930 --> 00:05:58,600
You guys are probably better off
talking without me.

109
00:05:59,270 --> 00:06:00,650
Have everything settled.

110
00:06:00,730 --> 00:06:03,020
-[all] Salute.
-[door closes]

111
00:06:05,820 --> 00:06:07,110
[Ji-seop sighs]

112
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:09,160
Does the general also like playing tennis?

113
00:06:10,410 --> 00:06:11,740
Hmm.

114
00:06:12,370 --> 00:06:13,200
Have a seat.

115
00:06:13,990 --> 00:06:15,200
Sit down. Have a seat.

116
00:06:16,540 --> 00:06:18,710
[Ji-seop] Goodness.
[groans]

117
00:06:19,710 --> 00:06:21,290
Is this everyone
in the investigation division?

118
00:06:21,380 --> 00:06:23,420
-[chief] Yes, that's right.
-I see. What about the soldiers?

119
00:06:23,500 --> 00:06:25,000
The administrative soldier
is in the office,

120
00:06:25,590 --> 00:06:27,920
and one of the D.P. soldiers
is in his barrack.

121
00:06:28,720 --> 00:06:30,640
[Ji-seop] Mm.
[puffs]

122
00:06:30,720 --> 00:06:33,970
Does that mean the other soldier
isn't in his barrack?

123
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:37,310
Well, the thing is…

124
00:06:40,060 --> 00:06:41,100
Officer.

125
00:06:41,190 --> 00:06:42,520
Yes, sir?

126
00:06:42,610 --> 00:06:44,440
When a superior asks you a question,

127
00:06:44,520 --> 00:06:48,320
you should organize your thoughts
and give a well-structured answer.

128
00:06:50,240 --> 00:06:52,740
I heard something happened recently.

129
00:06:54,740 --> 00:06:57,620
One of them is behind bars
for hitting a senior soldier.

130
00:07:00,290 --> 00:07:01,750
You left out why.

131
00:07:02,920 --> 00:07:04,590
[birds chirp]

132
00:07:05,420 --> 00:07:07,840
[footsteps approaching]

133
00:07:08,800 --> 00:07:10,840
[officer]
I heard you beat Park Sung-woo to a pulp.

134
00:07:12,890 --> 00:07:14,600
Good job.

135
00:07:15,180 --> 00:07:17,890
I hated how he showed off
for being a D.P. soldier.

136
00:07:19,140 --> 00:07:21,350
But even so, he's your senior,
you ungrateful jerk.

137
00:07:22,020 --> 00:07:23,810
[metal clanks]

138
00:07:23,900 --> 00:07:24,770
[officer] Hey, Nerd.

139
00:07:25,440 --> 00:07:27,400
Salute. You must be tired, sir.

140
00:07:27,480 --> 00:07:29,530
No, you're the one who's probably tired.

141
00:07:30,740 --> 00:07:32,450
You're pretty sturdy.

142
00:07:32,530 --> 00:07:34,280
Did you use to play sports?

143
00:07:34,370 --> 00:07:36,490
I did judo in middle school, sir.

144
00:07:36,580 --> 00:07:38,240
Oh, judo?

145
00:07:38,330 --> 00:07:39,540
Yes, sir.

146
00:07:39,620 --> 00:07:42,040
-Did you get to squeeze some boobs?
-No, sir.

147
00:07:42,120 --> 00:07:43,790
-Kimochi.
-No, sir.

148
00:07:43,880 --> 00:07:45,590
Don't get all fucking serious.

149
00:07:46,500 --> 00:07:47,630
[officer clicks tongue]

150
00:07:50,050 --> 00:07:52,260
-Lose some weight, okay?
-Yes, sir.

151
00:07:56,760 --> 00:07:58,970
-[yawns]
-Salute.

152
00:08:06,020 --> 00:08:07,400
My gosh.

153
00:08:08,110 --> 00:08:10,070
I heard you haven't been eating.

154
00:08:21,080 --> 00:08:22,460
Hurry up and take it.

155
00:08:31,710 --> 00:08:32,880
[Jun-ho] Thank you.

156
00:08:36,390 --> 00:08:38,680
CHOCO PIE

157
00:08:40,220 --> 00:08:42,230
CHEER UP!

158
00:08:42,310 --> 00:08:44,850
[Ji-seop] So that D.P. soldier
went to drink at a karaoke bar

159
00:08:44,940 --> 00:08:46,690
instead of catching the deserter.

160
00:08:47,480 --> 00:08:49,150
Meanwhile, the deserter died,

161
00:08:50,610 --> 00:08:52,820
and a junior beat his senior soldier?

162
00:08:52,900 --> 00:08:54,490
That's right, sir.

163
00:08:56,530 --> 00:08:58,370
Then have him dismissed.

164
00:08:59,330 --> 00:09:02,290
Yes, sir. I'll do it
once he gets out of military prison…

165
00:09:02,370 --> 00:09:03,250
[Ji-seop] No.

166
00:09:05,120 --> 00:09:06,620
His senior, not him.

167
00:09:08,040 --> 00:09:10,340
But the thing is, he's…

168
00:09:10,420 --> 00:09:11,300
What?

169
00:09:12,670 --> 00:09:14,380
Does he have connections?

170
00:09:18,390 --> 00:09:21,680
Park Sung-woo's dad, the district head,
will be stepping down next month.

171
00:09:24,520 --> 00:09:25,980
Let's keep it quiet.

172
00:09:27,940 --> 00:09:30,110
And try to focus
on improving your performance.

173
00:09:30,650 --> 00:09:32,400
The evaluation period is coming up.

174
00:09:34,990 --> 00:09:36,530
Yes, sir.

175
00:09:36,610 --> 00:09:37,910
Okay, good.

176
00:09:39,160 --> 00:09:41,530
Oh, and from now on,
you can report directly to me.

177
00:09:41,620 --> 00:09:42,950
[sighs]

178
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:46,250
Yes, sir.

179
00:09:51,170 --> 00:09:52,630
What should I do with An Jun-ho?

180
00:09:52,710 --> 00:09:53,630
[thuds]

181
00:09:54,130 --> 00:09:55,260
Who?

182
00:09:56,010 --> 00:09:57,380
[metal clanks]

183
00:10:04,890 --> 00:10:06,640
It's not the end of the world.

184
00:10:11,020 --> 00:10:12,190
I'm sorry.

185
00:10:13,070 --> 00:10:13,940
[Beom-gu] What?

186
00:10:16,190 --> 00:10:17,400
I'm sorry.

187
00:10:19,160 --> 00:10:20,490
What are you sorry for?

188
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:25,120
You asked me to bring him back…

189
00:10:26,290 --> 00:10:27,370
but I failed.

190
00:10:28,250 --> 00:10:29,540
So what?

191
00:10:31,540 --> 00:10:32,880
Pardon?

192
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:34,670
So what about that?

193
00:10:35,550 --> 00:10:37,260
What are you going to do about that?

194
00:10:41,050 --> 00:10:43,850
[sighs]
You can keep working as a D.P.

195
00:10:50,190 --> 00:10:51,650
[Jun-ho] But about Shin Woo-suk…

196
00:10:54,110 --> 00:10:56,480
He never would've deserted his post

197
00:10:58,240 --> 00:11:01,070
if he didn't join the army
in the first place.

198
00:11:05,830 --> 00:11:07,450
[Beom-gu] Does that even matter?

199
00:11:08,330 --> 00:11:10,670
[footsteps retreating]

200
00:11:10,750 --> 00:11:12,000
[Beom-gu] Get him out of there.

201
00:11:14,250 --> 00:11:15,340
[gate opens]

202
00:11:16,340 --> 00:11:17,630
[officer grunts]

203
00:11:20,050 --> 00:11:22,130
I can't believe this shit.

204
00:11:22,840 --> 00:11:25,720
How did he even get out?

205
00:11:27,390 --> 00:11:30,390
Jun-ho, be honest with me.

206
00:11:30,480 --> 00:11:32,060
Did you give Beom-gu a blowjob?

207
00:11:32,140 --> 00:11:33,520
[soldiers laugh]

208
00:11:33,600 --> 00:11:35,150
You did, right?

209
00:11:35,820 --> 00:11:38,320
[officer] Or did you let him fuck you?

210
00:11:38,400 --> 00:11:39,610
[soldiers laugh]

211
00:11:39,690 --> 00:11:41,490
[officer] Look at his face.

212
00:11:41,570 --> 00:11:44,410
Fucking bastard.
What's wrong with the military these days?

213
00:11:45,280 --> 00:11:46,910
What do you mean?

214
00:11:46,990 --> 00:11:48,950
Everything is just fine.

215
00:11:49,540 --> 00:11:52,160
[sudden music sting]

216
00:11:52,250 --> 00:11:53,620
What's going on?

217
00:11:55,040 --> 00:11:56,090
Am I invisible?

218
00:11:57,380 --> 00:11:58,880
[soldier 1] Corporal Han, you're back.

219
00:12:01,380 --> 00:12:03,130
Aren't you going to salute him?

220
00:12:03,220 --> 00:12:06,010
He's Corporal Han.
He's the one in charge of D.P.

221
00:12:06,100 --> 00:12:07,100
[soldiers] Salute.

222
00:12:07,180 --> 00:12:08,100
Salute.

223
00:12:08,180 --> 00:12:09,390
Nice to see you guys.

224
00:12:09,470 --> 00:12:11,850
Corporal Han, are you better now?

225
00:12:11,930 --> 00:12:12,810
I'm going to die.

226
00:12:13,480 --> 00:12:15,020
They say I'm terminally ill.

227
00:12:15,100 --> 00:12:16,900
I heard Sung-woo was dismissed.

228
00:12:17,690 --> 00:12:19,980
Because of that,
I have to take his place now.

229
00:12:20,780 --> 00:12:22,820
I guess I'll have to do what I'm told.

230
00:12:25,110 --> 00:12:27,490
Are you going to slack off
just like you did at the hospital?

231
00:12:27,580 --> 00:12:30,660
Yes, sir. I think I was born to slack off.

232
00:12:31,540 --> 00:12:33,500
I also love shrimp snacks.

233
00:12:36,880 --> 00:12:40,630
Sergeant Hwang.
Aren't you being discharged soon?

234
00:12:40,710 --> 00:12:43,760
Why do you keep acting like
you're the big shot here?

235
00:12:45,260 --> 00:12:46,260
Listen, Mr. Civilian.

236
00:12:47,340 --> 00:12:49,140
Do you have no respect for your senior?

237
00:12:49,220 --> 00:12:50,640
Didn't you know?

238
00:12:50,720 --> 00:12:54,140
When you're close to getting discharged,
you're no different from a civilian.

239
00:12:55,350 --> 00:12:58,690
You two D.P. assholes are pissing me off.

240
00:13:00,070 --> 00:13:02,150
One more word,
and I'll rip your mouth open.

241
00:13:06,450 --> 00:13:07,280
"One more word."

242
00:13:07,360 --> 00:13:09,030
-You asshole.
-[alarm beeps]

243
00:13:09,120 --> 00:13:10,740
It's 8:30 p.m.

244
00:13:11,330 --> 00:13:12,450
[alarm stops]

245
00:13:12,540 --> 00:13:14,620
Are you having a rap battle or something?

246
00:13:15,250 --> 00:13:18,960
I'm going to watch a TV show,
so shut the fuck up and sit down.

247
00:13:19,040 --> 00:13:20,210
[soldiers] Yes, sir.

248
00:13:20,290 --> 00:13:21,170
[Jeong-su] Good.

249
00:13:22,550 --> 00:13:26,800
[woman speaking on TV]

250
00:13:26,880 --> 00:13:30,760
Hey, you must be An Jun-ho, my junior.

251
00:13:30,850 --> 00:13:32,850
[woman speaking on TV continues]

252
00:13:34,560 --> 00:13:37,730
[quirky music plays]

253
00:13:37,810 --> 00:13:39,860
[slurps]

254
00:13:39,940 --> 00:13:41,110
Mm.

255
00:13:44,860 --> 00:13:46,820
The hot water melts the grease
from the noodles,

256
00:13:46,900 --> 00:13:50,200
and that grease melts the package,
which creates endocrine disruptors.

257
00:13:50,280 --> 00:13:51,780
It's really bad for you.

258
00:13:54,410 --> 00:13:55,790
[slurps]

259
00:13:55,870 --> 00:13:56,910
But it's delicious.

260
00:13:57,710 --> 00:13:59,630
It's so good that I can't stop eating.

261
00:14:00,580 --> 00:14:04,340
Maybe it tastes so good
thanks to all the endocrine disruptors.

262
00:14:04,420 --> 00:14:05,550
What do you think?

263
00:14:06,840 --> 00:14:07,880
I don't know, sir.

264
00:14:09,970 --> 00:14:11,600
I heard you beat up Sung-woo.

265
00:14:11,680 --> 00:14:13,890
[slurps]
Mm.

266
00:14:17,140 --> 00:14:18,600
Good job.

267
00:14:18,690 --> 00:14:19,690
You did good.

268
00:14:19,770 --> 00:14:21,400
I was sick, you see.

269
00:14:21,480 --> 00:14:24,110
I had problems breathing,
so I went to the medical corps,

270
00:14:24,190 --> 00:14:25,650
but they couldn't find the cause.

271
00:14:25,730 --> 00:14:27,150
The armed forces hospital couldn't either.

272
00:14:27,240 --> 00:14:29,030
But they wouldn't let me go
to a hospital outside.

273
00:14:29,110 --> 00:14:31,950
Meanwhile, Sung-woo was put in charge.

274
00:14:32,030 --> 00:14:34,620
And he loves to drink and party.

275
00:14:34,700 --> 00:14:36,580
Of course, everything's a mess.

276
00:14:36,660 --> 00:14:37,960
You're right, sir.

277
00:14:38,040 --> 00:14:41,630
Anyway, I'm different from him.
I do things in a new way.

278
00:14:41,710 --> 00:14:44,000
From now on,
you just need to do as I say, okay?

279
00:14:44,920 --> 00:14:45,920
Yes, sir.

280
00:14:46,010 --> 00:14:48,220
And don't get involved with those guys
in the barracks.

281
00:14:48,300 --> 00:14:49,760
They've got nothing to do with us.

282
00:14:49,840 --> 00:14:51,720
We just need to focus on our job.

283
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:53,930
Catching deserted soldiers.

284
00:14:55,180 --> 00:14:56,100
Yes, sir.

285
00:14:56,180 --> 00:14:59,230
I mean, how peaceful is this place?
No one's here to bully you.

286
00:14:59,310 --> 00:15:00,940
-[Beom-gu] D.P.
-[opens]

287
00:15:01,020 --> 00:15:03,020
Private An Jun-ho, sir.

288
00:15:03,110 --> 00:15:04,320
Corporal Han Ho-yeol.

289
00:15:04,400 --> 00:15:06,780
If you're done eating,
it's time to get to work.

290
00:15:09,030 --> 00:15:10,110
Yes, sir.

291
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:11,110
Yes, sir.

292
00:15:15,490 --> 00:15:18,700
[Beom-gu] His name is Choi Jun-mok.
He's been gone for two months.

293
00:15:20,120 --> 00:15:23,750
I think he was abused in his unit,
but we're not sure how.

294
00:15:25,130 --> 00:15:27,710
He was last spotted at a platform
in Incheon Station.

295
00:15:28,960 --> 00:15:30,590
He tried to commit suicide there.

296
00:15:30,670 --> 00:15:32,800
[horn honks]

297
00:15:32,890 --> 00:15:35,550
[train chugs]

298
00:15:35,640 --> 00:15:37,680
[horn honks]

299
00:15:38,470 --> 00:15:40,310
[conductor] Hey!

300
00:15:43,150 --> 00:15:44,230
Are you okay?

301
00:15:45,560 --> 00:15:48,570
-[ominous music plays]
-[indistinct PA chatter]

302
00:15:50,360 --> 00:15:52,400
INCHEON PLATFORM 1 CAR 4-2

303
00:15:53,860 --> 00:15:54,870
Got it?

304
00:15:56,080 --> 00:15:57,580
If it's been two months.

305
00:15:57,660 --> 00:15:59,450
We won't even have his access log.

306
00:15:59,540 --> 00:16:02,000
Did your mommy say you need that
to catch deserters?

307
00:16:02,080 --> 00:16:03,330
No, my aunt, sir.

308
00:16:03,920 --> 00:16:05,960
-Gi-yeong.
-[metal clatters]

309
00:16:06,040 --> 00:16:10,050
-Private First Class Heo Gi-yeong, sir.
-[Beom-gu] Get him the warrant.

310
00:16:10,130 --> 00:16:11,170
Go get it.

311
00:16:11,800 --> 00:16:12,680
Yes, sir.

312
00:16:12,760 --> 00:16:13,800
[objects clatter]

313
00:16:19,470 --> 00:16:21,230
[Gi-yeong] Second cabinet, third line.

314
00:16:26,150 --> 00:16:27,480
Thank you.

315
00:16:30,150 --> 00:16:31,900
AUTHORIZED PERSONNEL ONLY

316
00:16:33,030 --> 00:16:34,780
You can thank me with a Big Mac.

317
00:16:36,240 --> 00:16:37,320
I'm sorry, sir?

318
00:16:41,410 --> 00:16:43,830
If you want to thank me,
come back with a Big Mac.

319
00:16:44,580 --> 00:16:46,000
I want it with bacon, okay?

320
00:16:46,080 --> 00:16:48,040
[hums McDonald's theme's "I'm Lovin' It"]

321
00:16:48,130 --> 00:16:51,420
Private First Class Heo here
is always hungry.

322
00:16:52,010 --> 00:16:53,260
[Ho-yeol] Let's go.

323
00:16:53,340 --> 00:16:54,430
See you.

324
00:16:54,510 --> 00:16:55,880
[Ho-yeol] We'll be off now, sir.

325
00:16:56,720 --> 00:16:58,100
An Jun-ho.

326
00:16:58,180 --> 00:17:00,180
Private An Jun-ho, sir.

327
00:17:01,140 --> 00:17:03,600
[sucks teeth]
You'd better not take this for granted.

328
00:17:04,850 --> 00:17:06,480
[Beom-gu] You're not going on a picnic.

329
00:17:07,480 --> 00:17:08,730
Yes, sir.

330
00:17:10,730 --> 00:17:12,360
Don't get anyone killed.

331
00:17:13,820 --> 00:17:16,110
-[lighter clinks]
-[Beom-gu] And don't get killed either.

332
00:17:16,200 --> 00:17:17,700
[lighter clicks]

333
00:17:18,530 --> 00:17:19,830
[lighter clinks, thuds]

334
00:17:20,330 --> 00:17:21,540
Salute.

335
00:17:21,620 --> 00:17:22,490
Salute.

336
00:17:22,580 --> 00:17:25,910
STOP

337
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:30,630
-[birds chirp]
-[tranquil music plays]

338
00:17:39,470 --> 00:17:40,640
[Ho-yeol] What are you doing?

339
00:17:43,680 --> 00:17:44,930
Do you want me to go alone?

340
00:17:46,390 --> 00:17:47,270
No, sir.

341
00:17:51,400 --> 00:17:53,650
-Stay. Just stay.
-[Jun-ho] No, sir.

342
00:17:53,730 --> 00:17:55,360
[Ho-yeol] I'm fine alone.
Go have some shrimp snacks.

343
00:17:55,440 --> 00:17:57,700
-[Jun-ho] No, sir. I'm fine, sir.
-[Ho-yeol] Go have some snacks.

344
00:17:57,780 --> 00:18:00,280
I can do it alone. Go on back inside.

345
00:18:02,410 --> 00:18:04,410
Shouldn't we go
to the subway station first?

346
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:05,580
If he tries to kill himself…

347
00:18:05,660 --> 00:18:07,750
It's not easy to try again
when you stop while taking a shit.

348
00:18:07,830 --> 00:18:08,710
I'm sorry, sir?

349
00:18:08,790 --> 00:18:10,710
[Ho-yeol]
He'll need time to get ready again.

350
00:18:10,790 --> 00:18:13,300
Meanwhile, we're going to stick
to the basics.

351
00:18:13,880 --> 00:18:15,340
Step…

352
00:18:15,420 --> 00:18:16,260
by step.

353
00:18:16,840 --> 00:18:17,840
One at a time.

354
00:18:17,930 --> 00:18:19,590
Good. Step by step.

355
00:18:19,680 --> 00:18:21,050
Hello, sir.

356
00:18:21,140 --> 00:18:23,140
DEFENSE SECURITY COMMAND
REQUEST FOR DATA PROVISION

357
00:18:23,220 --> 00:18:26,430
[mysterious music plays]

358
00:18:26,520 --> 00:18:28,810
What do you think
that interception warrant is for?

359
00:18:30,600 --> 00:18:31,810
I'm not sure, sir.

360
00:18:31,900 --> 00:18:33,940
Normally…
[grunts]

361
00:18:34,020 --> 00:18:37,780
you use it to check the access log
of online games or search engines.

362
00:18:39,910 --> 00:18:41,870
Deserters tend to be hooked on video games

363
00:18:41,950 --> 00:18:44,990
or hopeless romantics who have
to send emails to their girlfriends.

364
00:18:45,080 --> 00:18:47,410
But in order to do that,
we need to visit each firm,

365
00:18:47,500 --> 00:18:49,500
fill in an application, and wait for days.

366
00:18:50,460 --> 00:18:53,420
And even if we get permission,
we need to access this site

367
00:18:53,500 --> 00:18:57,170
and pay for each and every information.

368
00:18:57,260 --> 00:18:58,920
Money makes the world go round.

369
00:18:59,720 --> 00:19:01,390
Do you understand what I'm saying?

370
00:19:01,470 --> 00:19:02,680
Yes, sir.

371
00:19:04,970 --> 00:19:06,350
You don't need to understand.

372
00:19:06,430 --> 00:19:07,390
I'm sorry, sir?

373
00:19:07,470 --> 00:19:09,350
Listen to me, Private An.

374
00:19:09,430 --> 00:19:12,520
What kind of a fool would use his own ID

375
00:19:12,600 --> 00:19:14,190
after having deserted from the army?

376
00:19:14,270 --> 00:19:16,940
They create new IDs
using other people's information.

377
00:19:18,900 --> 00:19:21,990
Then what do you think we need to do
to find the deserter?

378
00:19:24,660 --> 00:19:26,660
Three, two, one.

379
00:19:26,740 --> 00:19:28,160
-Well--
-Nope. Too late.

380
00:19:29,160 --> 00:19:30,910
We need to meet his acquaintances.

381
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:33,880
[Ho-yeol] Family, girlfriend, friends,
and alumni. It doesn't matter who.

382
00:19:33,960 --> 00:19:35,000
Anyone will do.

383
00:19:35,090 --> 00:19:37,920
"He's been out of touch. We're not close.
I don't talk to him."

384
00:19:38,010 --> 00:19:40,420
None of that matters.
Just question everyone.

385
00:19:41,970 --> 00:19:43,260
Why do you think we should?

386
00:19:44,090 --> 00:19:46,310
To predict what the deserter
might have done?

387
00:19:46,390 --> 00:19:47,760
No. Wrong answer.

388
00:19:48,390 --> 00:19:50,390
Deserters don't do the things
they normally do

389
00:19:50,480 --> 00:19:52,310
or things that are predictable.

390
00:19:52,390 --> 00:19:55,060
They intuitively know that it's dangerous.

391
00:19:56,820 --> 00:19:58,860
Jun-ho, you must not like fish cakes.

392
00:20:03,360 --> 00:20:04,570
Then is it the opposite?

393
00:20:06,240 --> 00:20:07,990
To avoid being predictable?

394
00:20:09,080 --> 00:20:10,040
Wrong again.

395
00:20:11,370 --> 00:20:13,620
[playful music plays]

396
00:20:13,710 --> 00:20:16,880
I thought you were smart.
What college do you go to?

397
00:20:18,340 --> 00:20:19,960
[Jun-ho] I don't go to college.

398
00:20:20,050 --> 00:20:21,010
[speaks Hangul]

399
00:20:26,260 --> 00:20:28,140
What a coincidence. Me neither.

400
00:20:28,220 --> 00:20:29,850
YONGDAM BUS TERMINAL

401
00:20:29,930 --> 00:20:31,350
Can you let go, sir?

402
00:20:33,140 --> 00:20:36,400
What we should do is,
we should think in their shoes.

403
00:20:37,230 --> 00:20:40,860
Find out what they'd want to eat,
who they'd want to see,

404
00:20:40,940 --> 00:20:42,490
and what may be on their minds.

405
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:44,780
It's what Hollywood actors do.

406
00:20:44,860 --> 00:20:48,120
It's called method acting.
Becoming one with the character.

407
00:20:48,200 --> 00:20:50,040
Doesn't that just mean
we're starting from scratch?

408
00:20:50,990 --> 00:20:52,410
Well, yes.

409
00:20:53,330 --> 00:20:55,920
Then what do you think is important
for us to do well?

410
00:20:57,420 --> 00:20:58,250
Stay persistent?

411
00:20:59,750 --> 00:21:01,260
Not be disappointed.

412
00:21:10,220 --> 00:21:11,560
[Ho-yeol] Why aren't you sleeping?

413
00:21:12,810 --> 00:21:14,850
I told you it's important
to get enough sleep.

414
00:21:17,400 --> 00:21:19,110
I just had something on my mind.

415
00:21:22,400 --> 00:21:24,490
But where are we going?

416
00:21:25,320 --> 00:21:26,860
Well…

417
00:21:28,070 --> 00:21:29,910
To meet the woman in his journal.

418
00:21:30,700 --> 00:21:34,620
[indistinct chatter]

419
00:21:41,380 --> 00:21:44,460
[woman] I already explained everything
to the last person who came.

420
00:21:44,550 --> 00:21:45,510
Mm-mmm.

421
00:21:46,680 --> 00:21:49,510
That's not why we're here today.

422
00:21:50,010 --> 00:21:51,640
Let me make myself clear.

423
00:21:51,720 --> 00:21:54,520
There was nothing between us.

424
00:21:54,600 --> 00:21:55,890
We only dated for a month.

425
00:21:55,980 --> 00:22:01,020
But Jun-mok thought of you
as his first love.

426
00:22:01,110 --> 00:22:02,440
What?

427
00:22:03,110 --> 00:22:04,740
Jun-ho, give me the journal.

428
00:22:06,990 --> 00:22:08,360
I don't have it, sir.

429
00:22:09,110 --> 00:22:09,950
You don't?

430
00:22:10,660 --> 00:22:12,870
I guess he forgot to bring it.

431
00:22:12,950 --> 00:22:14,950
In the army,
you're asked to write a journal.

432
00:22:15,040 --> 00:22:17,040
It's like a diary.

433
00:22:17,120 --> 00:22:18,460
And?

434
00:22:19,290 --> 00:22:20,290
Your name…

435
00:22:21,540 --> 00:22:23,090
was found in his journal, Ji-hye.

436
00:22:23,960 --> 00:22:25,170
What?

437
00:22:25,760 --> 00:22:26,760
[woman] Who?

438
00:22:27,470 --> 00:22:28,300
Then…

439
00:22:29,090 --> 00:22:31,510
I told you her name is Hye-jeong.

440
00:22:31,600 --> 00:22:34,100
Oh, right. Hye-jeong. That's right.

441
00:22:34,180 --> 00:22:37,180
He wrote tons of stuff about you
in his diary, Hye-jeong.

442
00:22:37,770 --> 00:22:38,600
Right?

443
00:22:42,110 --> 00:22:43,980
What did it say?

444
00:22:44,070 --> 00:22:45,730
I didn't read it in detail.

445
00:22:46,360 --> 00:22:50,450
But he wrote about how he fell for you
when you guys first met.

446
00:22:50,530 --> 00:22:52,660
[Ho-yeol] He wrote that he can
never forget that moment.

447
00:22:54,330 --> 00:22:57,910
You had jajangmyeon with him
at the orientation party, right?

448
00:23:00,460 --> 00:23:01,920
And what else?

449
00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:04,090
Oh, right. And…

450
00:23:04,960 --> 00:23:08,090
And he wrote that every moment
he spent with you

451
00:23:08,170 --> 00:23:10,470
was very special to him.

452
00:23:10,550 --> 00:23:12,010
[Ho-yeol] Yes, that's right.

453
00:23:12,550 --> 00:23:14,300
-He wrote that about me?
-Yes.

454
00:23:14,850 --> 00:23:15,970
[Hye-jeong] Really?

455
00:23:19,640 --> 00:23:21,440
I can't believe he wrote all that.

456
00:23:24,060 --> 00:23:26,860
So you want me to contact you
if Jun-mok ever calls, right?

457
00:23:26,940 --> 00:23:28,860
Yes, please call us.

458
00:23:28,940 --> 00:23:30,820
Okay. Bye.

459
00:23:30,900 --> 00:23:32,110
Bye.

460
00:23:37,330 --> 00:23:39,870
You're an amazing liar, sir.

461
00:23:40,460 --> 00:23:41,870
Who says I lied?

462
00:23:43,040 --> 00:23:44,290
[gasps]

463
00:23:47,130 --> 00:23:48,510
I had it.

464
00:23:49,970 --> 00:23:51,800
JOURNAL
REPUBLIC OF KOREA ARMY

465
00:23:53,760 --> 00:23:55,010
Ma'am, but Jun-mok…

466
00:23:55,100 --> 00:23:56,890
[woman] I don't remember!

467
00:23:56,970 --> 00:24:00,390
He just came here to eat chicken once
after he quit working here.

468
00:24:00,480 --> 00:24:01,940
Oh, you mean Acorn Jelly?

469
00:24:02,020 --> 00:24:02,940
Yes, Choi Jun-mok.

470
00:24:03,020 --> 00:24:05,980
I haven't seen him in months.

471
00:24:06,060 --> 00:24:07,360
Maybe he's started to lose faith.

472
00:24:07,440 --> 00:24:08,570
Get out of my way!

473
00:24:08,650 --> 00:24:10,070
[woman] Who are they talking about?

474
00:24:10,650 --> 00:24:11,740
He went to the army?

475
00:24:13,070 --> 00:24:14,450
Yes.

476
00:24:14,530 --> 00:24:16,120
I hope he returns soon.

477
00:24:22,160 --> 00:24:24,370
-You saw him a few days ago?
-Where?

478
00:24:24,460 --> 00:24:26,000
Where was it again?

479
00:24:26,080 --> 00:24:28,000
It was at a convenience store
at a subway station.

480
00:24:31,130 --> 00:24:33,630
[background chatter]

481
00:24:39,850 --> 00:24:41,100
Hey, Jun-mok.

482
00:24:43,140 --> 00:24:44,190
Jong-min.

483
00:24:45,060 --> 00:24:46,310
[Jong-min] Are you out on leave?

484
00:24:48,690 --> 00:24:49,520
What?

485
00:24:50,780 --> 00:24:51,900
Yes, I am.

486
00:24:52,990 --> 00:24:54,860
[Jun-ho] Did he seem a bit dark?

487
00:24:55,740 --> 00:24:57,160
[Jong-min] I'm not sure.

488
00:24:57,240 --> 00:24:59,240
I don't think so.

489
00:25:00,490 --> 00:25:01,950
[woman whimpers]

490
00:25:02,040 --> 00:25:04,660
My youngest son is very soft-hearted.

491
00:25:04,750 --> 00:25:06,580
[sobs]

492
00:25:07,330 --> 00:25:09,380
Where in the world could he be?

493
00:25:09,460 --> 00:25:13,760
He can't even sleep in strange places
because he's so sensitive.

494
00:25:13,840 --> 00:25:15,510
[whimpers]

495
00:25:16,090 --> 00:25:19,100
What if he gets so scared

496
00:25:19,180 --> 00:25:22,100
and ends up doing something bad
to himself?

497
00:25:22,180 --> 00:25:24,520
No, ma'am. That will never happen.

498
00:25:25,440 --> 00:25:27,650
[sobs]

499
00:25:27,730 --> 00:25:30,520
We'll bring him back
before anything like that happens.

500
00:25:30,610 --> 00:25:33,780
[woman cries]

501
00:25:34,690 --> 00:25:35,860
Hold on.

502
00:25:36,360 --> 00:25:37,570
Wait a minute.

503
00:25:38,070 --> 00:25:39,870
This isn't much.

504
00:25:40,410 --> 00:25:42,200
You remind me of Jun-mok.

505
00:25:42,290 --> 00:25:45,040
No, it's okay.
The military already gave us money.

506
00:25:45,120 --> 00:25:46,540
Sure, ma'am.

507
00:25:46,620 --> 00:25:49,790
We'll put this money to good use.
We promise we'll find Jun-mok.

508
00:25:52,170 --> 00:25:53,630
[woman] Please take good care of him.

509
00:25:55,470 --> 00:25:57,720
NO PLATFORM SCREEN DOORS
AT PREVIOUS TWO STATIONS

510
00:25:57,800 --> 00:25:59,930
Do you think Choi Jun-mok is okay?

511
00:26:00,850 --> 00:26:03,270
Jun-ho, do you smell yogurt?

512
00:26:04,850 --> 00:26:06,350
It's coming from your jacket.

513
00:26:06,890 --> 00:26:09,690
-I guess it's nicely fermented.
-It's probably rotten.

514
00:26:10,360 --> 00:26:12,150
How long have we been out?

515
00:26:12,230 --> 00:26:14,110
It's been 12 days.

516
00:26:14,190 --> 00:26:15,820
Is there anyone we haven't met yet?

517
00:26:16,990 --> 00:26:19,740
We met all his high school friends.

518
00:26:20,990 --> 00:26:22,280
[sighs]

519
00:26:22,370 --> 00:26:24,870
Don't worry. Jun-mok isn't dead.

520
00:26:26,790 --> 00:26:27,830
How are you so sure?

521
00:26:27,910 --> 00:26:29,620
He hasn't called yet.

522
00:26:30,330 --> 00:26:36,130
Nine out of ten suicidal deserters
call their mothers before they die.

523
00:26:37,760 --> 00:26:38,930
Ah.

524
00:26:40,930 --> 00:26:42,850
"Hi, I'm Choi Jun-mok.

525
00:26:42,930 --> 00:26:45,020
I'm 177cm tall. I weigh 70 kilograms.

526
00:26:45,100 --> 00:26:49,020
My vision is 1.2, but due to astigmatism
I wear glasses from time to time.

527
00:26:49,100 --> 00:26:50,900
My GPA is 2.7,

528
00:26:50,980 --> 00:26:54,520
and I got lucky and went to college
even though my grades were bad.

529
00:26:54,610 --> 00:26:57,610
I sometimes go to church
with my friends to play table tennis,

530
00:26:57,690 --> 00:27:02,280
and I joined the army after I broke up
with my first love in college.

531
00:27:02,950 --> 00:27:06,200
My dream is to become a public servant,
and my nickname is Acorn Jelly."

532
00:27:07,120 --> 00:27:08,410
Why "Acorn Jelly"?

533
00:27:09,370 --> 00:27:11,620
Because of his name

534
00:27:12,380 --> 00:27:13,920
and because he has no personality.

535
00:27:14,500 --> 00:27:17,050
"That's right. I have no personality.
Please find me."

536
00:27:17,130 --> 00:27:18,670
[dog barking tone from cell phone]

537
00:27:18,760 --> 00:27:19,880
You're getting a call.

538
00:27:20,760 --> 00:27:22,800
SERGEANT DOG

539
00:27:26,010 --> 00:27:28,640
Communications Security,
Corporal Han Ho-yeol, sir.

540
00:27:28,730 --> 00:27:30,940
[Beom-gu sighs]
Did you find anything?

541
00:27:31,020 --> 00:27:32,770
We're working on it, sir.

542
00:27:32,850 --> 00:27:36,690
That's your job, punk.
I'm asking if you made progress.

543
00:27:36,780 --> 00:27:39,280
[Ho-yeol]
Well, we're gathering information, sir.

544
00:27:39,360 --> 00:27:41,610
Are you kidding me?

545
00:27:41,700 --> 00:27:43,410
I want updates!

546
00:27:45,280 --> 00:27:46,740
Gosh, why is he yelling?

547
00:27:46,830 --> 00:27:49,080
What did you say, you punk?

548
00:27:49,660 --> 00:27:50,620
Ah.

549
00:27:51,410 --> 00:27:53,630
Nothing, sir. We'll find him.

550
00:27:54,630 --> 00:27:58,130
[Beom-gu groans] I received details on how
Choi Jun-mok was abused back in his unit.

551
00:28:01,340 --> 00:28:03,390
Jun-mok snores pretty loudly
when he sleeps.

552
00:28:04,140 --> 00:28:06,220
[snores]

553
00:28:06,300 --> 00:28:08,220
[Beom-gu]They made him wear a gas mask
and didn't let him sleep.

554
00:28:08,310 --> 00:28:10,770
[Jun-mok gasps, grunts]

555
00:28:11,480 --> 00:28:14,100
[grumbles]

556
00:28:16,270 --> 00:28:18,020
What a bunch of lunatics.

557
00:28:18,780 --> 00:28:19,900
Anything else, sir?

558
00:28:19,980 --> 00:28:24,200
Yes, he used his military debit card
to pay for a bowl of black bean noodles.

559
00:28:24,280 --> 00:28:26,370
[Beom-gu] A restaurant called Ilpoomhyang
in Ilsan, at 11:30 p.m.

560
00:28:28,080 --> 00:28:29,870
Don't bother to write it down.

561
00:28:29,950 --> 00:28:31,750
[Beom-gu] If you're not getting anywhere,
just come back.

562
00:28:31,830 --> 00:28:33,120
Yes, sir. Salute.

563
00:28:34,830 --> 00:28:38,040
Is he asking us to return?

564
00:28:38,130 --> 00:28:40,880
It means he'll kill us
if we go back empty-handed.

565
00:28:40,960 --> 00:28:42,380
How much money do we have left?

566
00:28:43,470 --> 00:28:46,510
We received 200,000 won,
and used it on food and transportation.

567
00:28:46,590 --> 00:28:47,430
So now…

568
00:28:47,510 --> 00:28:49,010
-[paper rustles]
-[coins chink]

569
00:28:50,010 --> 00:28:52,230
[Jun-ho] We have 7,800 won left.

570
00:28:53,180 --> 00:28:54,480
[scoffs]

571
00:28:55,060 --> 00:28:56,440
I'll use my secret weapon.

572
00:28:58,230 --> 00:28:59,860
24 HOUR SAUNA

573
00:28:59,940 --> 00:29:02,990
[Ho-yeol]
Sir, we're traveling the country on foot.

574
00:29:03,070 --> 00:29:04,150
And for some reason,

575
00:29:04,240 --> 00:29:07,070
the ATM machine is broken,
so we can't withdraw any money.

576
00:29:07,160 --> 00:29:08,530
If you let us in now,

577
00:29:08,620 --> 00:29:11,660
we'll withdraw money and pay you
as soon as the sun rises tomorrow.

578
00:29:13,080 --> 00:29:14,830
Where did you come from?

579
00:29:15,620 --> 00:29:16,460
Pardon?

580
00:29:16,540 --> 00:29:18,840
Where did you come from?
You said you're traveling on foot.

581
00:29:19,630 --> 00:29:23,130
We just moved to the city from Yeongwol,
so we're not familiar with the names…

582
00:29:23,210 --> 00:29:24,720
[scoffs]

583
00:29:24,800 --> 00:29:26,010
Where in Yeongwol?

584
00:29:26,090 --> 00:29:29,680
-[man] I'm from Yeongwol.
-A place called Deokpo…

585
00:29:30,760 --> 00:29:32,850
I'm from Deokpo. Where in Deokpo?

586
00:29:32,930 --> 00:29:34,560
It's near the Donggang River.

587
00:29:34,640 --> 00:29:38,940
-What?
-Once you walk past the army unit there…

588
00:29:39,020 --> 00:29:41,940
Oh, you mean the huge potato field
next to where people go rafting?

589
00:29:42,030 --> 00:29:43,530
I'm the youngest son of that family.

590
00:29:43,610 --> 00:29:45,320
-Oh, really?
-[chuckles]

591
00:29:45,400 --> 00:29:47,780
I'm telling you this
because we're all past this now.

592
00:29:48,360 --> 00:29:50,660
All the potatoes were ruined
because of that storm,

593
00:29:50,740 --> 00:29:52,290
so we couldn't sell them.

594
00:29:52,370 --> 00:29:53,790
My dad had a really tough time…

595
00:29:54,910 --> 00:29:56,250
due to Typhoon Maemi.

596
00:29:56,330 --> 00:29:57,170
What?

597
00:29:57,920 --> 00:29:59,750
The typhoon from two years ago
was Bolaven.

598
00:30:03,670 --> 00:30:05,010
My little brother…

599
00:30:06,760 --> 00:30:10,260
injured his head
when Typhoon Bolaven hit our town.

600
00:30:12,060 --> 00:30:13,140
[Ho-yeol] Sir.

601
00:30:13,220 --> 00:30:15,480
We're traveling the country on foot,

602
00:30:15,560 --> 00:30:18,100
and for some reason,
the ATM machine is broken…

603
00:30:18,690 --> 00:30:20,400
If you could let us in,
we'll withdraw money and…

604
00:30:20,480 --> 00:30:23,270
AN JUN-HO

605
00:30:28,820 --> 00:30:32,200
Sleep later. If you sleep now,
you won't be able to sleep past midnight.

606
00:30:32,870 --> 00:30:34,240
I'll sleep when I want to.

607
00:30:34,790 --> 00:30:35,790
Okay, fine.

608
00:30:38,120 --> 00:30:39,370
[sighs]

609
00:30:40,120 --> 00:30:41,580
[Ho-yeol] You were so good earlier.

610
00:30:41,670 --> 00:30:44,500
You should become an actor.

611
00:30:45,340 --> 00:30:47,170
I should get your autograph.

612
00:30:49,090 --> 00:30:51,010
Gosh, will you stop it already?

613
00:30:56,020 --> 00:30:57,680
There you go!
[laughs]

614
00:30:58,350 --> 00:31:00,060
-What will you do if I don't stop?
-[coughs]

615
00:31:01,100 --> 00:31:02,770
What will you do?

616
00:31:02,860 --> 00:31:05,110
-My gosh.
-I don't want to stop.

617
00:31:05,190 --> 00:31:06,360
Damn it.

618
00:31:06,440 --> 00:31:07,900
[Ho-yeol screams]

619
00:31:10,150 --> 00:31:11,990
There you go!
[laughs]

620
00:31:12,530 --> 00:31:14,530
There! There you go!

621
00:31:14,620 --> 00:31:18,080
[dramatic music plays]

622
00:31:20,920 --> 00:31:22,790
-Isn't it weird?
-What is?

623
00:31:24,090 --> 00:31:27,130
Why did he go all the way
to Incheon Station to attempt suicide?

624
00:31:27,710 --> 00:31:29,550
Because there are no screen doors there.

625
00:31:30,260 --> 00:31:33,090
The two previous stations
don't have screen doors either.

626
00:31:33,180 --> 00:31:34,300
Take a look at this.

627
00:31:34,890 --> 00:31:38,060
Choi Jun-mok's friend saw him at the store
in Sangildong Station.

628
00:31:38,140 --> 00:31:39,100
SANGILDONG STATION

629
00:31:39,180 --> 00:31:42,230
[Jun-ho]
And the Chinese restaurant he went to…

630
00:31:42,900 --> 00:31:45,400
[woman] This stop is the last stop.

631
00:31:45,480 --> 00:31:46,980
[Jun-ho]
It's right in front of Daehwa Station.

632
00:31:49,190 --> 00:31:50,610
The two stations…

633
00:31:50,700 --> 00:31:52,160
They're both the very last stations.

634
00:31:52,240 --> 00:31:53,530
He's a gourmet.

635
00:31:53,620 --> 00:31:55,410
He must enjoy searching for good food.

636
00:31:56,450 --> 00:32:00,330
Would you go searching for good food
in the middle of your suicide attempt?

637
00:32:00,410 --> 00:32:01,960
Why would you even say that?

638
00:32:02,040 --> 00:32:03,920
Here's another thing that's weird.

639
00:32:04,000 --> 00:32:07,000
Choi Jun-mok was always spotted
late at night.

640
00:32:07,670 --> 00:32:09,880
[Jun-ho] Incheon Station. 11:50 p.m.

641
00:32:09,960 --> 00:32:12,430
Sangildong Station. 12:15 a.m.

642
00:32:12,510 --> 00:32:14,300
Daehwa Station. 11:30 p.m.

643
00:32:15,850 --> 00:32:17,850
He's only active at nighttime.

644
00:32:19,520 --> 00:32:20,680
He's a vampire.

645
00:32:21,350 --> 00:32:22,230
Gosh.

646
00:32:23,650 --> 00:32:25,650
Then why don't you at least try to…

647
00:32:25,730 --> 00:32:27,610
[clicks tongue]
Come here.

648
00:32:29,900 --> 00:32:31,360
[keyboard clacks]

649
00:32:31,440 --> 00:32:35,450
I checked all the websites he signed up on
before and after he joined the army.

650
00:32:36,200 --> 00:32:37,990
Didn't you say this cost money?

651
00:32:38,080 --> 00:32:40,410
Yes, Jun-mok's mother gave us money.

652
00:32:41,410 --> 00:32:45,960
Anyway, I noticed
that he mostly used this as his ID.

653
00:32:49,130 --> 00:32:51,010
[Ho-yeol] It's "Black" without a "C."

654
00:32:51,090 --> 00:32:53,130
Choi Jun-mok's birthday is September 14.

655
00:32:53,220 --> 00:32:54,220
[Ho-yeol] Yes.

656
00:32:54,300 --> 00:32:56,550
But this ID had no login records.

657
00:32:56,640 --> 00:33:00,060
So I just looked up "blakmagic."

658
00:33:00,680 --> 00:33:02,890
And look. I got 470 results.

659
00:33:04,350 --> 00:33:07,150
I checked every single ID

660
00:33:07,230 --> 00:33:10,070
and compared all the personal information.

661
00:33:11,110 --> 00:33:12,030
Look.

662
00:33:13,280 --> 00:33:14,400
[Ho-yeol inhales deeply]

663
00:33:14,490 --> 00:33:15,570
[exhales]

664
00:33:16,070 --> 00:33:17,870
Doesn't this number look familiar?

665
00:33:18,780 --> 00:33:20,410
[Jun-ho] Four, eight,

666
00:33:20,490 --> 00:33:22,160
five, nine…

667
00:33:22,250 --> 00:33:25,580
So you want me to contact you
if Jun-mok ever calls, right?

668
00:33:25,670 --> 00:33:27,670
-Hye-jeong?
-[in English] Bingo.

669
00:33:28,290 --> 00:33:32,340
[in Hangul] So you're saying he just
typed in 111 for no reason and used…

670
00:33:34,880 --> 00:33:37,180
the number of that girl he liked
for the last four digits?

671
00:33:37,260 --> 00:33:39,600
[sucks teeth]
I'm not so sure about that.

672
00:33:39,680 --> 00:33:42,470
This is a better than guessing he went to
eat in the middle of his suicide attempt.

673
00:33:42,560 --> 00:33:43,810
Do you think so?

674
00:33:46,140 --> 00:33:49,560
[quirky music plays]

675
00:33:55,780 --> 00:33:57,320
[snores]

676
00:33:59,660 --> 00:34:01,080
[snoring continues]

677
00:34:08,750 --> 00:34:10,790
[cell phone buzzes]

678
00:34:10,880 --> 00:34:12,840
SLACKER

679
00:34:15,380 --> 00:34:16,800
Seriously?

680
00:34:16,880 --> 00:34:19,180
Communications Security,
Corporal Han Ho-yeol, sir!

681
00:34:20,010 --> 00:34:21,640
Have you lost it, you punk?

682
00:34:21,720 --> 00:34:23,140
No, sir.

683
00:34:23,930 --> 00:34:25,890
-[Beom-gu] What is it?
-Oh, well…

684
00:34:25,980 --> 00:34:28,020
We need another interception warrant.

685
00:34:28,100 --> 00:34:29,940
An Jun-ho took it with him.

686
00:34:30,020 --> 00:34:33,480
[Ho-yeol] No, not that one.
It's for someone else.

687
00:34:34,360 --> 00:34:35,440
[Beom-gu sighs]

688
00:34:35,530 --> 00:34:37,450
So you're saying Choi Jun-mok
created an ID

689
00:34:37,530 --> 00:34:40,200
using his ex-girlfriend's phone number?

690
00:34:41,030 --> 00:34:42,830
I mean, you think he might have?

691
00:34:43,450 --> 00:34:45,080
[coughs]

692
00:34:45,160 --> 00:34:46,370
That's right, sir.

693
00:34:46,870 --> 00:34:49,330
-[Beom-gu] Do you have evidence?
-It's based on confidence, sir.

694
00:34:49,420 --> 00:34:50,790
According to Jun-ho, at least.

695
00:34:52,250 --> 00:34:54,090
[Beom-gu] It sounds like
you're talking out of your ass.

696
00:34:55,090 --> 00:34:57,720
If this goes south, I'll get fired,
and you'll both be dead.

697
00:34:58,340 --> 00:34:59,550
[grunts]

698
00:34:59,630 --> 00:35:02,600
Yes, sir.
We'll just get dismissed with you, sir!

699
00:35:05,560 --> 00:35:06,640
You asshole!

700
00:35:06,720 --> 00:35:08,810
Private Heo Gi-yeong, sir.

701
00:35:10,600 --> 00:35:11,600
[Beom-gu sighs]

702
00:35:11,690 --> 00:35:15,190
[man singing on speaker]

703
00:35:17,820 --> 00:35:18,690
Salute.

704
00:35:18,780 --> 00:35:19,650
[Ji-seop] Oh, hey.

705
00:35:27,660 --> 00:35:29,160
Sir.

706
00:35:30,290 --> 00:35:33,670
We need an interception warrant
for a civilian.

707
00:35:34,340 --> 00:35:36,090
Hmm. Sure.

708
00:35:39,420 --> 00:35:40,630
Go ahead.

709
00:35:40,720 --> 00:35:42,010
Oh, okay.

710
00:35:42,090 --> 00:35:43,050
Thank you, sir.

711
00:35:44,140 --> 00:35:45,010
Okay.

712
00:35:45,100 --> 00:35:46,430
REQUEST FOR DATA PROVISION WARRANT

713
00:35:46,510 --> 00:35:51,270
[man singing on speaker continues]

714
00:35:53,900 --> 00:35:56,190
What's wrong? Did I say "okay" too easily?

715
00:35:56,270 --> 00:35:57,570
No, sir.

716
00:35:57,650 --> 00:36:01,110
I'm sure you're asking for it
because you're sure of something.

717
00:36:01,900 --> 00:36:05,530
Hey, issue a warrant
for Sergeant Park right away.

718
00:36:05,620 --> 00:36:06,450
[scoffs]

719
00:36:06,530 --> 00:36:07,700
[Ji-seop] Okay.

720
00:36:09,620 --> 00:36:11,120
Do you need anything else?

721
00:36:11,710 --> 00:36:13,500
No. Thank you, sir. Salute.

722
00:36:13,580 --> 00:36:15,040
Salute.

723
00:36:18,880 --> 00:36:19,960
[door closes]

724
00:36:21,630 --> 00:36:23,130
[chuckles]

725
00:36:25,720 --> 00:36:28,850
That fucking bastard…
[scoffs]

726
00:36:32,600 --> 00:36:33,690
Hey.

727
00:36:33,770 --> 00:36:35,560
Send the location to the D.P. soldiers

728
00:36:36,110 --> 00:36:38,110
and tell them I wasn't kidding earlier.

729
00:36:38,650 --> 00:36:40,690
They're dead if they don't catch him.

730
00:36:40,780 --> 00:36:43,280
[upbeat music playing]

731
00:36:50,660 --> 00:36:52,830
Everything will be fine. Don't worry.

732
00:36:52,910 --> 00:36:54,000
Okay? Don't be nervous.

733
00:36:54,080 --> 00:36:55,420
Got it, sir.

734
00:36:56,330 --> 00:36:59,880
Did you memorize the Miranda rights?
Don't get nervous and make a mistake.

735
00:36:59,960 --> 00:37:01,090
Okay, sir.

736
00:37:04,090 --> 00:37:05,470
Are you nervous, sir?

737
00:37:06,050 --> 00:37:07,220
Of course, you punk.

738
00:37:07,930 --> 00:37:09,600
I'll still be nervous
even after a hundred arrests.

739
00:37:09,680 --> 00:37:10,720
[sniffles]

740
00:37:12,890 --> 00:37:15,060
[woman] Hello, are you a member here?

741
00:37:18,190 --> 00:37:20,730
[whispers]
No, we're not. We're the military police.

742
00:37:21,570 --> 00:37:23,280
[Jun-ho] Is there a back entrance here?

743
00:37:23,360 --> 00:37:24,610
No, there isn't.

744
00:37:30,370 --> 00:37:33,200
[mysterious music plays]

745
00:37:43,380 --> 00:37:44,260
[whispers]
I'm sorry.

746
00:37:49,300 --> 00:37:50,680
What do you want?

747
00:37:51,260 --> 00:37:52,270
I'm sorry.

748
00:37:53,020 --> 00:37:54,230
It's okay.

749
00:37:57,310 --> 00:37:59,400
Did you enjoy this?
Let me clean it up for you.

750
00:38:06,490 --> 00:38:08,610
[ominous music plays]

751
00:38:24,210 --> 00:38:25,550
[woman] Hey, you two!

752
00:38:25,630 --> 00:38:28,840
Stop fooling around and leave or I'll
report you for obstruction of business.

753
00:38:30,260 --> 00:38:31,100
Damn it.

754
00:38:32,260 --> 00:38:35,730
[suspenseful music plays]

755
00:38:35,810 --> 00:38:36,730
My gosh.

756
00:38:49,320 --> 00:38:50,950
What do you want?

757
00:38:51,490 --> 00:38:52,830
[man] Who are you people?

758
00:38:55,160 --> 00:38:57,710
-Ah. Uh…
-I'm sorry.

759
00:38:57,790 --> 00:39:00,460
I'm sorry.
You look just like my friend, Jun-mok.

760
00:39:00,540 --> 00:39:02,590
-I thought you were Jun-mok…
-My gosh.

761
00:39:02,670 --> 00:39:05,090
[Ho-yeol]
I'm sorry. Sorry for troubling you.

762
00:39:05,170 --> 00:39:06,590
I'll push your seat back in.

763
00:39:06,670 --> 00:39:08,550
You can go back to sleep.

764
00:39:14,510 --> 00:39:17,850
Let's not be disappointed.
There's no need to be disappointed.

765
00:39:17,930 --> 00:39:19,270
Vampire…

766
00:39:20,020 --> 00:39:23,310
[Ho-yeol]
Back to ground zero. We can do this.

767
00:39:23,400 --> 00:39:24,270
Where is he?

768
00:39:24,360 --> 00:39:26,400
I think I know where Choi Jun-mok is.

769
00:39:27,860 --> 00:39:28,740
What?

770
00:39:32,110 --> 00:39:33,620
[Jun-mok snores]

771
00:39:33,700 --> 00:39:37,450
[mysterious music plays]

772
00:39:44,630 --> 00:39:46,920
[soldier 1]
Hey, wake that buddy fucker up.

773
00:39:47,420 --> 00:39:48,550
[gasps]

774
00:39:49,970 --> 00:39:51,590
[Jun-ho] He is a vampire.

775
00:39:52,340 --> 00:39:55,600
[mysterious music playing continues]

776
00:39:58,220 --> 00:40:01,730
[Jun-ho] Choi Jun-mok was always found
at the last stop late at night

777
00:40:01,810 --> 00:40:03,850
when the subway closes.

778
00:40:04,360 --> 00:40:06,980
[mysterious music plays]

779
00:40:07,070 --> 00:40:08,400
-[sighs]
-[Ho-yeol sucks teeth]

780
00:40:08,480 --> 00:40:11,110
So instead of trying to do anything
at his destination,

781
00:40:14,200 --> 00:40:16,200
he just fell asleep
and found himself there?

782
00:40:17,790 --> 00:40:19,450
Then what about his suicide attempt?

783
00:40:20,500 --> 00:40:22,710
[train approaching]

784
00:40:22,790 --> 00:40:24,380
[snores]

785
00:40:26,670 --> 00:40:28,500
[train horn honks]

786
00:40:28,590 --> 00:40:29,630
[conductor] Hey!

787
00:40:36,760 --> 00:40:39,520
[electricity crackles]

788
00:40:59,990 --> 00:41:01,120
Did you sleep well?

789
00:41:03,660 --> 00:41:05,250
Where am I?

790
00:41:06,670 --> 00:41:08,000
The last stop.

791
00:41:09,960 --> 00:41:11,670
The last stop of subway line two.

792
00:41:12,550 --> 00:41:13,800
I see.

793
00:41:15,630 --> 00:41:17,850
I guess this is the end of the line.

794
00:41:21,020 --> 00:41:23,480
[cuffs clinking]

795
00:41:27,190 --> 00:41:28,730
I'm sorry.

796
00:41:30,360 --> 00:41:32,820
[cuffs clinking]

797
00:41:38,740 --> 00:41:40,580
What's on your mind?

798
00:41:43,250 --> 00:41:44,540
Just…

799
00:41:46,920 --> 00:41:49,540
That it's so comfortable here.

800
00:41:54,590 --> 00:41:56,970
-[birds chirp]
-[Beo-gum yawns]

801
00:41:59,430 --> 00:42:00,760
[soldiers pants]

802
00:42:04,100 --> 00:42:05,480
[Beom-gu] What are you doing here?

803
00:42:07,230 --> 00:42:08,350
We're planting trees.

804
00:42:09,190 --> 00:42:10,020
What?

805
00:42:11,070 --> 00:42:12,440
It's not even Arbor Day.

806
00:42:12,530 --> 00:42:15,190
[sighs]
The general asked us to plant them.

807
00:42:15,280 --> 00:42:17,280
He thinks the barracks look too deserted.

808
00:42:17,910 --> 00:42:19,280
Where did you get that tree?

809
00:42:19,370 --> 00:42:20,200
Well…

810
00:42:21,160 --> 00:42:22,700
we dug it out from over there.

811
00:42:24,120 --> 00:42:25,450
[gasps]

812
00:42:25,540 --> 00:42:27,290
[officer speaks Hangul]

813
00:42:27,370 --> 00:42:28,210
[soldiers] Yes, sir.

814
00:42:28,290 --> 00:42:31,210
You're a special forces soldier.
Why can't you do this properly?

815
00:42:31,290 --> 00:42:35,210
I want you to dig a hole,
not caress the damn soil.

816
00:42:35,300 --> 00:42:37,590
-How is this so hard?
-How fucking absurd.

817
00:42:37,680 --> 00:42:40,050
[cell phone buzzes]

818
00:42:40,140 --> 00:42:41,350
[exhales]

819
00:42:43,310 --> 00:42:44,520
How did it go?

820
00:42:44,600 --> 00:42:46,730
-[Ho-yeol] We arrested Choi Jun-mok.
-Really?

821
00:42:46,810 --> 00:42:47,940
[Beom-gu] Where?

822
00:42:48,850 --> 00:42:50,650
We found him on the street.

823
00:42:51,770 --> 00:42:53,150
You prick.

824
00:42:55,360 --> 00:42:57,150
Anyway, good work. Hurry up and return.

825
00:42:57,240 --> 00:42:59,200
Yes, sir. Salute.

826
00:43:03,240 --> 00:43:05,120
McDonald's.

827
00:43:07,290 --> 00:43:08,660
This is for Private Heo Gi-yeong.

828
00:43:09,250 --> 00:43:10,250
I know.

829
00:43:12,380 --> 00:43:13,670
Baked eggs?

830
00:43:14,460 --> 00:43:15,420
[Jun-ho] Do you want one?

831
00:43:18,760 --> 00:43:20,930
I guess you don't like eggs.

832
00:43:22,930 --> 00:43:24,760
[cell phone buzzes]

833
00:43:24,850 --> 00:43:26,640
[Ho-yeol] It's gone bad. My gosh.

834
00:43:27,810 --> 00:43:29,140
[Jun-ho] Oh, hello.

835
00:43:29,850 --> 00:43:30,770
Yes.

836
00:43:32,060 --> 00:43:33,440
Okay, just a moment.

837
00:43:36,070 --> 00:43:37,110
Your girlfriend.

838
00:43:39,780 --> 00:43:41,200
My girlfriend?

839
00:43:48,700 --> 00:43:50,080
[Jun-mok stammers] Hye-jeong.

840
00:43:56,340 --> 00:43:57,380
Mom.

841
00:43:58,590 --> 00:44:00,590
[dramatic music playing]

842
00:44:18,610 --> 00:44:21,740
I'm sorry, Mom.
[cries]

843
00:44:25,820 --> 00:44:27,370
[sobs]

844
00:44:27,450 --> 00:44:28,540
I'm sorry.

845
00:44:32,250 --> 00:44:33,370
[Jun-mok sniffles]

846
00:44:34,500 --> 00:44:37,250
[dramatic music playing continues]

847
00:45:03,200 --> 00:45:05,240
[gate clanks]

848
00:45:16,000 --> 00:45:19,210
[lighter clicking]

849
00:45:25,010 --> 00:45:27,720
CELL 5

850
00:45:34,480 --> 00:45:37,270
[rain patters]

851
00:45:42,400 --> 00:45:45,110
[ominous music plays]

852
00:45:47,110 --> 00:45:49,030
I'm sorry, but can I borrow your lighter?

853
00:45:56,420 --> 00:45:57,620
[clicks]

854
00:46:04,720 --> 00:46:06,430
[Woo-suk puffs]

855
00:46:08,390 --> 00:46:09,300
Are you doing okay?

856
00:46:11,260 --> 00:46:12,260
Well…

857
00:46:14,350 --> 00:46:15,430
I'm not sure.

858
00:46:17,520 --> 00:46:18,400
No.

859
00:46:20,560 --> 00:46:22,440
I'm asking if you're okay

860
00:46:23,820 --> 00:46:25,400
that you've killed someone.

861
00:46:26,030 --> 00:46:29,200
[ominous music playing continues]

862
00:46:40,040 --> 00:46:43,420
GUEST APPEARANCE BY
LEE JOONG-OK

863
00:46:44,130 --> 00:46:48,010
[somber music playing]

864
00:49:20,120 --> 00:49:22,450
[music ends]